body:
@bbejeck Thanks for the shared benchmarks. They were really helpful.

One thing that I am not clear is that with 10 sec commit interval, flushing is actually significantly better than no-flushing (i.e. G43/44 and J43/44); I would expect that they do not have obvious difference in this case, and I'm wondering if it is just the variance of the benchmark itself? E.g. how many runs have you done for each comparison, and did the experiment have enough data to sustain at least 10 seconds (I remember the SimpleBenchmark only 10M records in total).

Once that is cleared I think this patch is good to go.
